<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Compilation Principles Course">
  <data key="d0">Compilation Principles Course</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Compilation Principles Course is a university-level specialized theoretical educational course centered on compiler-related knowledge. Its core curriculum introduces the basic principles and core, fundamental implementation technologies and techniques for constructing programming language compilers, alongside additional key topics including the formal definition of compilers, the significance of learning compilation principles, compiler design, compiler operation principles, end-to-end compilation processes, and different compiler classifications. It is designed to systematically teach learners targeted professional knowledge about compilation programs and compilation theory.

As a formal open e-learning MOOC, the Compilation Principles Course is developed and delivered by an instructor from the National University of Defense Technology, and hosted on the China University MOOC platform. All of its learning content is released in the form of pre-recorded formal lecture videos paired with corresponding supporting lecture slides, which serve as the source material for any related analyzed lecture slides and course video clips derived from the course. One of its publicly documented lesson segments is the 1.1.1 What is a Compiler chapter, for which a captured video frame has been logged at the 06:11 timestamp of that specific lecture recording.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bff27f0e3ebb48b2fea68269a0c7f4e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b8d7f49d2d77540a7d48ffec2cd30a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff0eb7c8503f6f576c5dbe6ae9289e07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c6b2705ec167d0d2cbb72ed2e06acd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f91f380996e15a6befe44b116b504c49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d85f67b63626aec731c1a8a42c23b26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8e9bdfcd6b3158e92bbf122d402684d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0bf72583d5f3299c35639a94e7b4680&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e71864bdc455486075a3b9359689cec7</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935568</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Translator Program">
  <data key="d0">Translator Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A software program that equivalently transforms a program written in one language into a program written in another language.&lt;SEP&gt;A foundational compiler technology related concept, explained as a prerequisite before introducing the definition of a compiler program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbe9bd011edad6122f4088d39bccd833</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Source Language">
  <data key="d0">Source Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The original input language used to write the program that will be processed by a translator program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Source Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Source Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A program written in the source language that serves as the input for a translator program.&lt;SEP&gt;The input language program that is equivalently processed and converted by a translation program, highlighted in red font in the course slide.&lt;SEP&gt;The input program written in the original source language, which is processed by the translator to generate the target equivalent program, highlighted in red on the lecture slide.&lt;SEP&gt;The input program written in the original source programming language, which is directly processed by the interpreter for interpretation and execution.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ace17451e5dffc278bca17ca541aeac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0bf72583d5f3299c35639a94e7b4680&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e71864bdc455486075a3b9359689cec7</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Target Language">
  <data key="d0">Target Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The output language that the input source language program is transformed into by a translator program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Target Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Target Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An equivalent program written in the target language generated by a translator program from the source language program.&lt;SEP&gt;The semantically equivalent output language program generated by a translation program, highlighted in red font in the course slide.&lt;SEP&gt;The equivalent output program generated by the translator after processing the source language program, highlighted in red on the lecture slide.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ace17451e5dffc278bca17ca541aeac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e71864bdc455486075a3b9359689cec7</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compiler Program">
  <data key="d0">Compiler Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A specific type of translator program that equivalently converts a high-level language program into a low-level language program.&lt;SEP&gt;The core teaching subject of the compiler principles course, whose formal definition is introduced immediately after the explanation of the translator program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbe9bd011edad6122f4088d39bccd833</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High Level Programming Language">
  <data key="d0">High Level Programming Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The human-readable, abstract source language processed by a standard compiler program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low Level Programming Language">
  <data key="d0">Low Level Programming Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The machine-oriented target language generated by a standard compiler program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Assembly Language">
  <data key="d0">Assembly Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A symbolic, human-understandable type of low-level programming language corresponding to raw machine instructions.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Machine Language">
  <data key="d0">Machine Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A binary raw instruction type of low-level programming language that can be directly executed by computer hardware.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diagnostic Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Diagnostic Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A specialized compiler designed to help programmers develop and debug programs, prioritizing error detection and troubleshooting.&lt;SEP&gt;An upcoming sub-topic related to compiler classification that is introduced in the analyzed lecture frame right after the basic compiler definition.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the three special types of compiler listed on the course lecture slide.&lt;SEP&gt;The first of the four listed categories of compilers on the educational lecture slide, with a provided Chinese name and corresponding English translation.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Optimizing Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Optimizing Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A specialized compiler that focuses on improving the execution efficiency of the generated target code.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the three special types of compiler listed on the course lecture slide.&lt;SEP&gt;The second of the four listed categories of compilers on the educational lecture slide, with a provided Chinese name and corresponding English translation.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Host Machine">
  <data key="d0">Host Machine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The computer system that runs the compiler program in use.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Target Machine">
  <data key="d0">Target Machine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The computer system that runs the generated target language program output by a compiler.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cross Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Cross Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A specialized compiler that generates machine code for a target machine different from its running host machine.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the three special types of compiler listed on the course lecture slide.&lt;SEP&gt;The third of the four listed categories of compilers on the educational lecture slide, with a provided Chinese name and corresponding English translation.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Retargetable Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Retargetable Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A specialized compiler that can generate target code for different platforms by modifying only machine-related parts, no need to rewrite machine-independent sections.&lt;SEP&gt;The fourth of the four listed categories of compilers on the educational lecture slide, which the lecturer is currently explaining and can generate code for different target platforms.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Interpreter Program">
  <data key="d0">Interpreter Program</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of program that sequentially translates each statement of the original program into machine instructions, executes it, and proceeds to the next statement until all statements are processed to obtain the full program execution result.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of translator that processes source programs directly, translating and executing each statement sequentially without generating a separate complete target program file.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-001</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compiler Working Process">
  <data key="d0">Compiler Working Process</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The step-by-step operation workflow followed by a compiler program to transform source code into equivalent target code.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Internal Compiler Architecture">
  <data key="d0">Internal Compiler Architecture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The modular component layout that constitutes the internal organizational structure of a standard compiler program.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Typical Compiler Generation Approaches">
  <data key="d0">Typical Compiler Generation Approaches</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A set of common standardized techniques used to develop and implement new compiler programs.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compilation">
  <data key="d0">Compilation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A program translation mode that produces a complete, full equivalent translated version of the entire source document before the executor uses the translated content.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the two core program processing paradigms whose difference from interpretation is explained on the target presentation slide.&lt;SEP&gt;A core professional concept in the field of compilation principles, which is marked as the correct answer corresponding to option A in the quiz.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-001&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff0eb7c8503f6f576c5dbe6ae9289e07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3f1b3f06c8ce4771c7bfcaf0a483156</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Interpretation">
  <data key="d0">Interpretation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A program translation mode that translates each individual sentence of the source document one by one, where the executor operates immediately after each single translation, and no full equivalent translated version of the entire source document is generated.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the two core program processing paradigms whose difference from compilation is explained on the target presentation slide.&lt;SEP&gt;A core professional concept in the field of compilation principles, which is set as the unselected alternative answer corresponding to option B in the quiz.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-0964c36c2f3a13d4fcb742a671a493fd-chunk-001&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff0eb7c8503f6f576c5dbe6ae9289e07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3f1b3f06c8ce4771c7bfcaf0a483156</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
