<node id="Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of translator program that performs equivalent conversion between high-level programming languages and low-level programming languages.&lt;SEP&gt;A program that performs the translation operation to transform high-level language programs into equivalent machine language programs, explained in the lecture frame&lt;SEP&gt;A computer program that equivalently converts a high-level language program to another low-level language program such as assembly language program or machine language program.&lt;SEP&gt;A program that equivalently converts high-level language programs to low-level language programs such as assembly or machine language.&lt;SEP&gt;A program that equivalently converts high-level language programs to low-level programs such as assembly or machine language.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c5ed2b863510eafd5fecdb97b44f6dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d85f67b63626aec731c1a8a42c23b26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Level Language Program">
  <data key="d0">High-Level Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A program written in high-level programming languages that acts as the source input for a compiler.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of program written in high-level programming language, highlighted in red in the lecture frame content&lt;SEP&gt;A type of computer program written in high-level programming language, that acts as the input for the standard compilation process.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of program that serves as the input for a compiler's translation process, highlighted in red on the lecture slide.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c5ed2b863510eafd5fecdb97b44f6dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d85f67b63626aec731c1a8a42c23b26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Level Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Low-Level Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A program written in low-level languages such as assembly language or machine language, which is the output generated by a compiler.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of program that includes assembly language and machine language programs, marked in red with descriptive explanatory notes in the frame&lt;SEP&gt;A type of computer program written in low-level programming language, that is the converted output generated by a compiler from a corresponding high-level language program.&lt;SEP&gt;A category of program that is the target output of a compiler's translation process, including forms like assembly or machine language, highlighted in red on the lecture slide.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c5ed2b863510eafd5fecdb97b44f6dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d85f67b63626aec731c1a8a42c23b26</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Machine Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Machine Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Another specific example type of low-level language program that a compiler can generate as output per the slide definition.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific type of low-level language program that can be directly executed by a computer's central processing unit.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific category of low-level language program that a compiler generates as output, explicitly called out and highlighted in the lecture content&lt;SEP&gt;A specific type of low-level language program that is generated after translating a high-level language program, to be executed to produce the final result.&lt;SEP&gt;A category of directly executable low-level language program generated by the compiler after processing the input high-level language program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c5ed2b863510eafd5fecdb97b44f6dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d85f67b63626aec731c1a8a42c23b26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781935555</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
