<edge source="High-Level Language Program" target="Machine Language Program">
  <data key="d7">3.0</data>
  <data key="d8">A high-level language program is translated through the compilation workflow to produce a corresponding executable machine language program.&lt;SEP&gt;The high-level language program is translated through the defined translation step to generate the machine language program as shown in the slide's process flow diagram.&lt;SEP&gt;The input high-level language program is processed and translated by the compiler to generate the corresponding machine language program.</data>
  <data key="d9">Translate to,Translated To,converted into,generate,translated to</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-5f5328057af8271fffc25a5e04150084&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e10eb17b787da3ec7998622b93eaf3cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23a5e3ba82916d8142a93c48d5f886c</data>
  <data key="d11">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d12">1781935568</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Low-Level Language Program" target="Machine Language Program">
  <data key="d7">2.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The category of low-level language programs explicitly includes machine language programs as a representative example in the compiler definition.&lt;SEP&gt;Low-level language program category explicitly covers machine language programs as one of its core sub-types</data>
  <data key="d9">Categorizes,Includes,cites as example,includes</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-5c5ed2b863510eafd5fecdb97b44f6dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8d85f67b63626aec731c1a8a42c23b26</data>
